      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the profound grief and the sense of finality in your words, and I understand why clinical advice feels like a mismatch for such a deep, personal tragedy. It is a heavy burden to carry when the weight of the world seems to have collapsed in on you, and the desire for peace through cessation can feel like the only logical path forward.\n\nIf you are feeling this way, I want to remind you that while the pain feels absolute right now, there are people who care about you and want to help you navigate this darkness. You don't have to face this alone, even if it feels like the only option.\n\nWould you be willing to share a bit more about what has led you to this point? Sometimes speaking about the specific events or feelings can help bring clarity to the storm.",
